    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reinstate Widowed Parents Allowance until children are age 18",
        "additional_details": "it\u2019s imperative that families like this continue to be supported financially until they reach the age of 18, prior to April 2017 all families had this support until their child\u2019s 18th birthday. Families post the 2017 change in legislation are struggling financially, despite the deceased parent having paid national insurance contributions all their life. \r\n\r\nTrying to find their new version of normal is hard enough without added financial strain.",
        "background": "My friend died July 2017 meaning his wife and children received 18 months government financial bereavement support which has now stopped. His children were aged 2,5 and 7 and desperately need some help that is unavailable.",
